{
  "stem": "12491.3",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "One of them, who is my cousin, managed to get into the latrine and submerge himself up to his neck in the dirt, and stayed there till the children on the trucks were removed from the camp.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Then he returned, and we managed to hide him from the Germans until he was evacuated from Plaszow.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Actually, he managed to go with me to-- to Schindler's.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But the Schindler's-- the-- the SS commandant at Schindler's camp refused to keep children.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Therefore, he sent out all the children to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So he was only about two or three weeks at Schindler's.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "At that point, he was removed.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "To me?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I eventually was-- in the beginning of November, or middle of November, was-- the people on the list were assembled on a plaza, taken, on-- put on a train, and transported to a concentration camp, Gross-Rosen, which is in southeastern Germany, where we stayed for several days.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was a horrible camp.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But because we were on the list, and because Schindler has made arrangements, to us it was only a transit camp.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We spent a few days.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We were shaven-- I mean, our heads were shaven.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And our uniforms were taken away-- I mean, the-- the striped uniforms taken away, and we were going through a shower room, and come out through the other end, and gave-- given new uniforms.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So nobody could really smuggle anything with him.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, I had hidden-- and you'll have to pardon me, my word-- I had hidden a $50 bill in my rectum, and a $10 gold piece taped to my foot, under my foot.",
      "word_count": 37
    }
  ],
